textDelta: When was the Star Spangled Banner written? The Star-Spangled Banner was written on September 14, 1814.
During which war was the Star Spangled Banner written? The War of 1812.

Clinton administration's Russian economy policy The Clinton administration's Russian economy policy was to encourage private enterprise and foreign investment in the Russian economy. The administration also worked to reduce Russian debt and to promote economic reform.
Where did Frederick Cook explore in 1909? Cook explored the North Pole in 1909.

Why do countries try to protect their firms from exposure to the world market? There are a few reasons why countries might try to protect their firms from exposure to the world market. One reason is that the country may want to ensure that its firms are able to compete in the global market. Another reason is that the country may want to protect its firms from competition from foreign firms.
What is true of a spontaneous process? A spontaneous process is a process that does not require input from outside the system.
What is a spontaneous process? A spontaneous process is a process that occurs without any outside interference.
What happens to entropy in a spontaneous process? The entropy of a system always increases in a spontaneous process.
